<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[813,1453,1192,1568]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,940,1192,1216]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,933,1192,1216]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Discussion</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
— The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[1102,1236,1193,1216]" class="Insecta" family="Nepidae" genus="Cercotmetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1102,1236,1193,1216]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Cercotmetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains 10 species (exclusive of subspecies) occurring in Asia and 
<collectingCountry box="[1304,1404,1224,1248]" name="Australia" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Australia</collectingCountry>
. The taxonomy was competently revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lansbury, I" box="[1219,1396,1256,1280]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="83 - 106" refId="ref19429" refString="Lansbury, I., 1973. A review of the genus Cercotmetus Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 (Hemiptera - Heteroptera: Nepidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 116: 83 - 106." type="journal article" year="1973">Lansbury (1973)</bibRefCitation>
, with only 
<taxonomicName authority="Keffer &amp; J. Polhemus" authorityName="Keffer &amp; J. Polhemus" authorityYear="1999" box="[865,1208,1288,1312]" class="Insecta" family="Nepidae" genus="Cercotmetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis box="[865,883,1289,1312]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[894,978,1289,1312]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">minutus</emphasis>
Keffer &amp; J. Polhemus
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1269,1320,1288,1311]" name="Laos" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Laos</collectingCountry>
having been subsequently described. Unlike other nepids, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Nepidae" genus="Cercotmetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1318,1453,1321,1344]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Cercotmetus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
occur along the margins of flowing streams, where they may sometimes be observed swimming near shore. The individual species are solitary in their habits, and not generally collected in large numbers. As such, the geographic ranges of the constituent taxa are still incompletely understood, and the records provided below serve to fill in a number of distributional gaps.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[813,1453,1608,2048]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Key morphological apomorphies defining 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[1284,1420,1609,1632]" class="Insecta" family="Nepidae" genus="Cercotmetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1284,1420,1609,1632]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Cercotmetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lansbury, I" box="[955,1138,1640,1664]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="83 - 106" refId="ref19429" refString="Lansbury, I., 1973. A review of the genus Cercotmetus Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 (Hemiptera - Heteroptera: Nepidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 116: 83 - 106." type="journal article" year="1973">Lansbury (1973)</bibRefCitation>
include the outer margin of the eyes sloping downward and obscuring the ventral margin of the head, the length of the fore femur shorter than the prothorax, the middle and hind tibiae with fringes of long swimming hairs, and the phallotheca housed in a membranous anterior diverticulum rather than within the sclerotized genital capsule. The eggs of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[1059,1196,1833,1856]" class="Insecta" family="Nepidae" genus="Cercotmetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1059,1196,1833,1856]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Cercotmetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bear slender, elongate respiratory horns that are much longer than the egg itself, being in some cases up to 
<quantity box="[1110,1188,1896,1920]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
in length (see 
<figureCitation box="[1357,1422,1896,1920]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[812,847,2061,2083]" captionTargetBox="[812,1453,1071,2039]" captionTargetId="figure-368@1.[812,1454,1068,2039]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Lethocerus indicus (Lepeletier &amp; Serville), male, specimen from Laos, Vientiane Prov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5351510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5351510/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[1409,1422,1896,1920]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" unit="in" value="1.0">1</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lansbury, I" box="[813,982,1928,1952]" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" pagination="83 - 106" refId="ref19429" refString="Lansbury, I., 1973. A review of the genus Cercotmetus Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843 (Hemiptera - Heteroptera: Nepidae). Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 116: 83 - 106." type="journal article" year="1973">Lansbury, 1973</bibRefCitation>
). Similar respiratory horns are also found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1790" box="[813,900,1961,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Nepidae" genus="Ranatra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,900,1961,1984]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Ranatra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but are shorter that those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[1227,1361,1961,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Nepidae" genus="Cercotmetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1227,1361,1961,1984]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Cercotmetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, at least in all tropical Asian 
<taxonomicName box="[1026,1196,1992,2016]" class="Insecta" family="Nepidae" genus="Ranatra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1026,1113,1993,2016]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="28">Ranatra</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
for which this character state is known.
</paragraph>
